                        <div class="detaildropdown-conten">
                           <button class="detailfaq-question">
                              <img src="assets/img/iconh/20.png" alt="Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)" width="35px" loading="lazy">&nbsp;&nbsp;
                              <div class="question-text-wrapper">
                                 <span class="question-text">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) Bali Pass Trek </span>
                                 <span class="question-subheading">Your Curiosity, Our Commitment</span>
                              </div>
                              <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                           </button>
  
                           
                           <div class="detaildropdown-content">
                                                                                          <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>1. What is the Bali Pass Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The Bali Pass Trek is a high-altitude Himalayan trek in Uttarakhand that connects Har Ki Dun Valley to Yamunotri Valley. Known for its raw beauty, challenging trails, and panoramic views, it is one of the most adventurous treks in the Indian Himalayas.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>2. Where is the Bali Pass Trek located?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Bali Pass is located in the Govind National Park, Uttarkashi district of Uttarakhand. The trek route passes through Sankri, Taluka, Osla, Har Ki Dun, Ruinsara Tal, and ends near Yamunotri.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>3. What is the altitude of Bali Pass?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The Bali Pass summit stands at an altitude of 4,950 meters (16,240 feet), making it a high-altitude and challenging trek.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>4. What is the best time to do the Bali Pass Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    • Summer (May – June): Best for clear skies, green meadows, and snow at higher altitudes.
• Post-monsoon (September – October): Crystal-clear mountain views and stable weather.
Not recommended in monsoon (July–August) due to heavy rainfall and landslides.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>5. What is the duration of the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The trek generally takes 8–9 days, including travel to and from the base village Sankri.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>6. What is the difficulty level of Bali Pass Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Bali Pass is a difficult trek suitable only for experienced trekkers. It involves:
• Steep ascents and descents
• High-altitude walking above 4,500 m
• Snow patches and glacier crossings                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>7. What should I pack for the Bali Pass Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    • Trekking shoes with good grip
• Layered warm clothing (thermal, fleece, down jacket)
• Rain gear (poncho/jacket)
• Trekking pole, headlamp, gloves, and woollen socks
• Sunscreen, sunglasses, and water bottles                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>8. Is it safe to trek Bali Pass?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Yes, it is safe if done with proper preparation and a professional guide. Since it’s a high-altitude trek, risks like altitude sickness, steep trails, and unpredictable weather exist, so safety measures and acclimatization are essential.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>9. What is the highlight of the Bali Pass Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    • Crossing the Bali Pass Summit (4,950 m)
• Stunning views of peaks like Swargarohini, Bandarpoonch, and Kalanag
• Ruinsara Tal Lake – a high-altitude glacial lake
• Walking through Har Ki Dun and Yamunotri valleys                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>10. What kind of fitness is required?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Trekkers should have prior high-altitude trekking experience and good stamina. Regular cardio exercises, stair climbing, and strength training are recommended 2–3 months before the trek.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>11. Is Bali Pass Trek suitable for beginners?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    No. This trek is recommended only for experienced trekkers because of its steep climbs, snow crossings, and high altitude. Beginners should attempt easier treks like Kedarkantha or Har Ki Dun first.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>12. Can Bali Pass Trek be done in winter?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    No. Winter trekking is not possible due to heavy snowfall, blocked routes, and extreme cold. Best months remain May–June and September–October.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                                                       </div>
                        </div>
                     </div>
